						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Sixth pillar in Ark-Killāh.</hi></p>						

						<p>A.D. 1241.</p>						

						<p>This inscription is dated in <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1162, Śārvari, Pushya Amāvāsyā, Sunday</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1241, January 13, Sunday.</hi></p>						

						<p>It records a grant of land and certain taxes by <hi rend="italic">Sarvādhikāri</hi> <hi rend="bold">Bhāgubāyi</hi> to the worship and offerings of god <hi rend="bold">Narasimhadēva</hi> of <hi rend="bold">Vijayāpura.</hi></p>						

